ee  Joy .  It was strongly revived in the 19th century under the influence of popular fiction. It is borne by characters in Mrs  Henry Wood's  East Lynne (  1861 ) and  Edna Lyall's  In the Golden Days (  1885 ). Modern use may well have been influenced also by the common Irish surname derived from the medieval Norman male name.  See also  Joss ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Joyce de Huntingfield was born about 1266, in England, United Kingdom. She married Roger de Herling. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1266–":"umbes 1266–Surnud","1268–Male":"1268–Surnud","1282–1346":"1282–1346","1266–Female":"1266–Surnud","about 1282":"umbes 1282","1346":"1346","1268":"1268","1266":"1266","about 1266":"umbes 1266","1282":"1282","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1266–":"noin 1266–Kuollut","1268–Male":"1268–Kuollut","1282–1346":"1282–1346","1266–Female":"1266–Kuollut","about 1282":"noin 1282","1346":"1346","1268":"1268","1266":"1266","about 1266":"noin 1266","1282":"1282","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1266–":"environ 1266–Décédée","1268–Male":"1268–Décédé","1282–1346":"1282–1346","1266–Female":"1266–Décédée","about 1282":"environ 1282","1346":"1346","1268":"1268","1266":"1266","about 1266":"environ 1266","1282":"1282","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Joyce de Huntingfield est née environ 1266, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Roger de Herling. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1266–":"um 1266–Verstorben","1268–Male":"1268–Verstorben","1282–1346":"1282–1346","1266–Female":"1266–Verstorben","about 1282":"um 1282","1346":"1346","1268":"1268","1266":"1266","about 1266":"um 1266","1282":"1282"